Text.Value: Gnome-pricks: you're off the hook. Scram, before I get my senses.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Addressed to the room in general
EditorData.NodeContext: Addressed to the room in general

Text.Value: Understood. I won't interfere.
The gnomes should be able to go where they please. They are not the duergar's to keep.
RELEASE. THE. GNOMES. IMMEDIATELY.
The gnomes go free. You get to live. Everybody wins.
Leave.
Mm - you got a point. Likely to be all hobbled up, what with the lashings.
You do that.
And there ain't no way I'm sticking around long enough to meet him.
What makes Moonrise Towers such a threat?
You can't be serious. What the fuck is wrong with you?
Clan property. They come with us.
And the slaves? What about them?

EditorData.logicalname: At least one gnome still alive

Text.Value: Time I scrammed before more pricks from Moonrise Towers move in.
Here's your cut. I always keep my word. ([6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
Please. We catch your scent, and you'll get sliced 'fore you can bat your left eye.
Mm. For a jargh, you got smarts.
Won't hear me argue. Your mouth's got the might to back it.
Set them free, or I will thrash you like I thrashed Nere.
The way I hear tell, some prick there calls the shots. The General, Nere called him.
Hardly. They drag their feet, and I'll scorch their arses. Works every time.
Your brain going mushy, jargh? That's where those Absolute-freaks hole up.
Have you no heart? They deserved freedom - and you denied it.
Clan: grab your gear, wipe your arses.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Addressed to the room in general
EditorData.NodeContext: Addressed to the room in general
EditorData.logicalname: at least one other rebel still alive.

Text.Value: Speak up, chief. You can't just let the clan keep them.
Brittle are the foundations upon which the houses of tyrants are built. It seems I judged you to be less brittle than you really are.
Then do it, ya shit. We'll see who thrashes who.
Try it, ya uppity shit, see what happens.
Get moving. If I see you slavers again, I'll tear you apart.
Good idea. I'll start by adding your corpse to the pile.
Goblins, drow, gnolls, even humans - ain't no one they won't try to turn.
Leave - and take the slaves with you. Before I change my mind.
Here's your cut. Extra too, like I promised. ([463b0f43-5410-412d-aba3-875cf81c38ca])
Come at me, ya shit.
Very well. I'll rummage what I can.
Sschindylryn's shithouse - you see it? Cock-stench had a wriggler in his skull. All the more reason to clear out.
No way we're letting these bastards take those gnomes. Right?
And the gold you owe me?

EditorData.logicalname: Didn't have enough gold - needs flag

Text.Value: Now lug your arse someplace else - I got to get cracking.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Addressed to the room in general.

Text.Value: Your wish is my command, jargh.
I am freeing these gnomes. Just try and stop me.
Someone's gone pickin' my pockets, ya chaff. You want coin, there's plenty of corpses to sack.
Let the gnomes go. They'll just slow you down.
Born to serve, my father said. I'll keep 'em busy.
Good idea. They're a valuable asset.

Synopsis: The mutinous duergar tells the player what comes next for them: an assault on Moonrise Towers.
